5 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Volatile revenue -- transfer to Montana growth and opportunity
6 trust. (1) Starting in the fiscal year beginning July 1, 2027, and in each subsequent fiscal year by November 1,
7 the state treasurer shall transfer one-half of the amount of volatile revenue from the general fund for that fiscal
8 year to the Montana growth and opportunity trust established in [section 1].
9 (2) The amount of volatile revenue is an amount equal to:
10 (a) the sum of capital gains volatile revenue and partnership volatile revenue; and
11 (b) a portion of interest earnings from the treasury cash account in 17-6-202 as calculated
12 pursuant to subsection (3).
13 (3) The amount of interest earnings from the treasury cash account in 17-6-202 to be transferred
14 as volatile revenue pursuant to subsection (2) is the difference between:
15 (a) the estimate of interest earnings on the treasury cash account in 17-6-202 as provided in the
16 most recent official revenue estimate provided for in 5-5-227; and
17 (b) the lowest actual amount of interest earnings on the treasury cash account in 17-6-202 within
18 the most recent 10 years of available data as certified to the legislative fiscal analyst and the budget director by
19 the department of administration.
20 (4) For the purposes of this section, the following calculations apply:
21 (a) "Capital gains increment" is the difference between:
22 (i) the current calendar year's capital gains estimate as described in the most recent official
23 revenue estimate provided for in 5-5-227; and
24 (ii) the lowest reported capital gains income from any year within the most recent 10 years of
25 available data, as published in the department of revenue's biennial report provided for in 15-1-205.
26 (b) "Capital gains volatile revenue" is calculated by multiplying the capital gains increment by the
27 rate established in 15-30-2103(2)(a)(ii).
28 (c) "Partnership increment" is the difference between:
